ay.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 12:58:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/baicalein-alleviates-iron-overload-induced-ferroptosis-and-osteogenic-blockade-in-osteoblasts-by-activating-the-nrf2-gpx4-pathway</guid></item><item><title>小小的冰冻世界竟然出现了气氛</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/tiny-frozen-world-unexpectedly-appears-to-have-an-atmosphere</link><description>一个与冥王星轨道相似、宽 500 公里的天体挑战了我们关于太阳系外层小天体的假设&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/tiny-frozen-world-unexpectedly-appears-to-have-an-atmosphere2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 12:43:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/tiny-frozen-world-unexpectedly-appears-to-have-an-atmosphere</guid></item><item><title>透氧右旋糖酐纳米凝胶作为血红蛋白氧载体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/oxygen-permeable-dextran-nanogels-as-a-hemoglobin-based-oxygen-carrier</link><description>刚刚发表：透氧性右旋糖酐纳米凝胶作为血红蛋白氧载体&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/oxygen-permeable-dextran-nanogels-as-a-hemoglobin-based-oxygen-carrier.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 12:28:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/oxygen-permeable-dextran-nanogels-as-a-hemoglobin-based-oxygen-carrier</guid></item><item><title>首个针对帕金森病的个性化大脑修复</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-first-personalized-brain-repair-for-parkinsons</link><description>帕金森病是一种重复性的震颤、僵硬、运动缓慢的模式，最终依赖于缓解（但永远不会停止）衰退的药物。但如果该脚本不再固定怎么办？如果大脑实际上可以根据患者自身的生物学特征进行重建，而不是在其恶化时对其进行仔细管理，会怎么样？ &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/the-first-personalized-brain-repair-for-parkinsons.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 12:13:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/the-first-personalized-brain-repair-for-parkinsons</guid></item><item><title>传播异磁之爱</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/spreading-the-altermagnetic-love</link><description>根据理论，一种称为交变磁性的特性可以通过与交变磁体相邻的非磁性材料获得。&lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/spreading-the-altermagnetic-love2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 11:58:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/spreading-the-altermagnetic-love</guid></item><item><title>了解激光如何快速磁化聚变等离子体</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/understanding-how-lasers-can-rapidly-magnetize-fusion-plasmas</link><description>通过一组新的模拟，确定了可以导致快速膨胀的等离子体（聚变能源系统中利用的超热物质状态）自发产生自己的磁场的机制。这提高了我们对宇宙中自然产生的等离子体的理解，并促进了基于直接驱动惯性聚变方法的聚变系统的发展。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/understanding-how-lasers-can-rapidly-magnetize-fusion-plasmas2.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 11:43:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/understanding-how-lasers-can-rapidly-magnetize-fusion-plasmas</guid></item><item><title>基于大脑的指数可能揭示 30 岁成年人患阿尔茨海默病的风险模式</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-based-index-may-reveal-alzheimers-risk-patterns-in-adults-as-young-as-30</link><description>在过去的几十年里，世界各地的神经科学家和医学研究人员一直试图利用现有的健康记录、脑部扫描和其他医学数据来发现与特定疾病或神经精神疾病发作相关的生物标记。这些生物标志物的识别可以帮助设计新的工具来预测个体患者出现特定病症的风险，从而使医生能够及早干预，预防或延迟其出现或减缓其进展。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/brain-based-index-may-reveal-alzheimers-risk-patterns-in-adults-as-young-as-30.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 11:28:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/brain-based-index-may-reveal-alzheimers-risk-patterns-in-adults-as-young-as-30</guid></item><item><title>800 名被监禁男子的大脑内部：高度精神病与大脑表面积扩大有关</title><link>https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/inside-the-brains-of-800-incarcerated-men-high-psychopathy-linked-to-expanded-brain-surface-area</link><description>具有高度精神病倾向的人通常无法对其他人产生同理心。从脑科学的角度来看，同理心不是单一的情感，而是一个多部分的神经过程。它涉及帮助我们分享他人感受、理解他们的观点、甚至在精神上融入他们的经历的大脑系统。 &lt;img src="https://lifeboat.com/blog.images/inside-the-brains-of-800-incarcerated-men-high-psychopathy-linked-to-expanded-brain-surface-area.jpg" /&gt;由 PolitePaul 服务提供</description><pubDate>Wed, 06 May 2026 11:13:17 GMT</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="true">https://lifeboat.com/blog/2026/05/inside-the-brains-of-800-incarcerated-men-high-psychopathy-linked-to-expanded-brain-surface-area</guid></item></channel></rss>